For those who don't know, Claude (created by @AnthropicAI) is an intelligent AI chatbot similar in nature to ChatGPT (GPT-3.5 + GPT-4). 

While there are many technical aspects to what differentiates Claude from other AI models, the two things that matter most for me (and probably for you) are the following:

1. Speed
Claude is fast. Like REALLY fast. Even with the non-instant versions of Claude it outpaces GPT by leaps and bounds.

With faster responses you can get more done with less waiting around.

2. Context Length
For those who aren't aware, all AI chatbots have limited memory of a conversation's history—this is called the Context Length. For GPT-3.5 (standard ChatGPT) that Context Length is ~3,000 words. For GPT-4 it's ~6,000 words. For Claude's 100k model, the Context Length is 75,000 words. 🤯

That means deeper conversations that can go on for a LONG time without the AI "forgetting" earlier pieces of the conversation.
